  "outcome": "A notifier creates and submits a CHED-PP from scratch (CHEDPP.GB.2026.1525998), then uses 'Copy as new' from the notifications dashboard to clone it into a fresh draft, edits the copied commodity/consignment/transport/document/address data, and submits the copy (CHEDPP.GB.2026.1526007); the test then switches to a second browser context as a BIP inspector, finds the copied CHED on 'Assess consignments', opens it, and FAILS after 30s because the 'Record PHSI checks' button never rendered on the BIP Notification overview — so the B2B inspection leg never ran.",
  "notes": [
    "Two distinct journeys in one trace: actions 10-93 = original CHED-PP creation + submit; actions 94-145 = copy-as-new of that CHED + edit + submit; actions 148-155 = BIP inspector leg (failed).",
    "Copy-as-new lands the user directly on the copied draft's Notification Overview hub (action 100) with commodities already populated — no 'What are you importing?' / origin / commodity-search pages are re-walked.",
    "The copy journey re-walks only: Commodity details, Consignment Details, Transport Before BIP, Goods movement services, Contact details, Nominated Contacts, Documents, Addresses, Review, Declaration.",
    "Failure evidence: on the BIP Notification overview at action 155 the only buttons present were 'Save and set as in progress', 'Attachments', 'Return to work order' — no 'Record PHSI checks'.",
    "Deliberate data divergence between original and copy proves the copy is independently editable: net weight 1 -> 10, quantity 1 -> 2, total gross weight 12 -> 100, controlled-atmosphere container Yes -> No, transport doc ref 'certificate' -> 'Phytosanitary certificate', document ref REF-124 -> REF-123, doc date 04/12/2025 -> 16/06/2026, arrival minutes 15 -> 13.",
    "Address handling differs between the two journeys: the original creates a consignor from scratch then uses 'Same as consignee'; the copy inherits addresses and only clicks '#populate-place-of-destination'.",
    "The 'Controlled atmosphere container' control is a select reached via getByText, not a checkbox; underlying values are 'on'/'off'.",
    "The 'finished-or-propagated' control is located by a CSS suffix selector (no accessible name available) — a11y gap worth noting.",
    "Network log in this trace is worker-scoped and contains CHEDA/CHEDD/CHEDP traffic from sibling tests; the flat request list is NOT reliable for correlating URLs to this test's actions. Page identity below is derived from frozen-DOM page titles; the URLs were recovered per-action from each action's own navigation log (`trace action <id>` -> 'navigated to \"...\"'), which IS action-scoped and therefore reliable.",
    "Two hosts are in play: the B2C notifier service at importnotification-static-snd.azure.defra.cloud (/notification/...) and the B2B inspector service at importnotification-int-static-snd.azure.defra.cloud (/decision/...). Uploads sit on a third path prefix (/upload/...) on the notifier host.",
    "Draft IDs are allocated at the first save (DRAFT.GB.2026.1525998 appears from action 15, i.e. after the origin page) and become CHEDPP.GB.<year>.<n> on submit. Copy-as-new mints a NEW draft ID (DRAFT.GB.2026.1526007) — the copy is a separate record from the start, not a mutation of the original."
